value.value: A rare carcinoma of the skin. It is characterized by epidermoid cells interspersed with glandular cells.
A poroma characterized by the presence of small nodules of neoplastic cells in the superficial dermis without connection to the epidermis.

label.value: Benign Mixed Tumor of the Skin

value.value: A rare, benign, slow-growing and painless neoplasm of sweat glands. It usually arises in the head and neck. It is characterized by the presence of a mesenchymal chondroid stroma, fibrosis, and epithelial structures.
A benign, intermediate, or malignant neoplasm that arises from the dermis.
